        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 2 at 10:18PM MDT until August 2 at 10:30PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 1018 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 10 miles north of
Nara Visa, moving southeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Ping pong ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect
wind damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Mainly rural areas of Southeastern Union County.
</description>
        <instruction>Seek shelter inside a well-built structure and stay away from
windows. This storm is capable of producing damaging winds and large
hail.

Motorists can expect brief but sudden changes in visibility and
ponding of water on roadways as storms move through the area.</instruction>
